ğŸ­ Terraform Conditional Expressions â€“ Smart Infra Logic
ğŸ§  What Are Conditional Expressions?
A conditional expression in Terraform is like an if-else for configuration. It lets you dynamically decide a value based on a condition.

Format:

hcl
Copy
Edit
condition ? true_value : false_value
ğŸ”§ Basic Syntax
hcl
Copy
Edit
variable "env" {
  default = "prod"
}

locals {
  instance_type = var.env == "prod" ? "t3.large" : "t3.micro"
}
âœ… If env = "prod", result = "t3.large"
âŒ Else, result = "t3.micro"

âš™ï¸ Common Use Cases
Use Case	Example
Select values based on environment	Instance type, tags, AMIs
Toggle resource creation	Count = condition ? 1 : 0
Conditional variables	enable_feature ? var.feature_val : null
Custom naming	name = var.is_test ? "test-instance" : "main-instance"

ğŸ§ª Real Examples
âœ… 1. Conditional Resource Creation
hcl
Copy
Edit
resource "aws_instance" "optional" {
  count = var.create_instance ? 1 : 0
  ami           = var.ami
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
}
âœ… 2. Conditional Tags
hcl
Copy
Edit
tags = {
  Environment = var.env
  CostCenter  = var.env == "prod" ? "C123" : "Test"
}
âœ… 3. Optional Output
hcl
Copy
Edit
output "db_url" {
  value = var.enable_db ? "db.prod.example.com" : "no-db"
}
âš ï¸ Gotchas to Avoid
Mistake	Fix
Using booleans directly in count	Always use ? 1 : 0 instead of true/false
Using null where not allowed	Some resources donâ€™t support null, use "" or 0
Forgetting type compatibility	Both true/false branches must return the same type

ğŸ§  In Interviews: Be Ready For
Question	Smart Answer Sample
â€œHow do you create optional resources?â€	â€œUsing count with conditional expressions like count = var.enabled ? 1 : 0â€
â€œHow do you manage values across environments?â€	â€œUsing var.env == 'prod' ? high-value : low-value expressionsâ€
â€œHow to avoid errors when resource is not used?â€	â€œUse conditionals with count and try() to safely access valuesâ€

âœ… Bonus: With try() for safer conditionals
hcl
Copy
Edit
output "az" {
  value = try(aws_instance.web.availability_zone, "not available")
}
ğŸ Summary Table
Expression	Meaning
var.env == "prod" ? "yes" : "no"	Basic conditional
var.enabled ? 1 : 0	Use in count to toggle resources
condition ? var.value : null	Dynamic variable usage
var.env != "prod" ? "dev-ami" : "prod-ami"	Select AMIs based on environment




